%% Diagram: Service Worker lifecycle states
%% Type: state
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Parsed: register()

    Parsed --> Installing: install event
    Installing --> Installed: waitUntil resolves
    Installing --> Redundant: install rejects

    Installed --> Activating: no clients OR skipWaiting()
    Installed --> Waiting: existing SW controls clients

    Waiting --> Activating: old SW unregistered\nor clients reload

    Activating --> Activated: activate handler resolves
    Activating --> Redundant: activate rejects

    Activated --> Idle: no events in flight
    Idle --> Activated: fetch / push / sync\nresets idle timer
    Idle --> Redundant: ~30s idle\n(UA may terminate)

    Redundant --> [*]

    note right of Idle
        Termination is browser-controlled.
        Use waitUntil() inside an
        ExtendableEvent to keep the
        worker alive until work settles.
    end note
